1тГгShowing off is Shirk
2тГгBowing for other than Allah is Haram
3тГгImitating non-Muslims in worship or non-worship (customs, symbol, acts, habit, mannerism, dressing, gestures (dabbing, Nae Nae dance) peculiar to them & common among corrupt people, musicians, oppressors, politicians etc.) or promotes corruption directly or indirectly is prohibited.
4тГгDoubtful symbolism & secrecy is forbidden.
ЁЯШЗThere is no doubt that this gesture of dabbing on folks is a way to show-off . Al-Musnad, Mahmoud ibn Labeed said: The Messenger of Allah (sallAllaahu тАШalayhiwasallam) said: тАЬThe thing that I fear most for you is minor shirk.тАЭ They said: тАЬO Messenger of Allah, what is minor shirk?тАЭ He said: тАЬShowing off, for Allah will say on the Day when people are recompensed for their actions: тАШGo to those for whom you were showing off with your deeds in the world, and see what reward you find with them.тАЩтАЭ (saheeh). Prophet said: тАЬShirk among you will be more subtle than the footsteps of an ant, but I will teach you something which, if you do it, both minor and major shirk will be kept away from you. Say: *Allaahumma inni aтАЩoodhu bika an ushrika bika wa ana aтАЩlam wa astaghfiruka lima la aтАЩlam (O Allaah, I seek refuge with You from associating anything with You knowingly, & I seek Your forgiveness for that of which I am unaware).тАЭ (Saheeh al-Jaami)* One should realize that showing off destroys all one's actions (i.e., cancels out the reward), and that it brings the wrath of Allaah. The wise person does not waste his energy in doing things that do not bring any reward, let alone deeds that bring the wrath and anger of Allah. Just as there will be a punishment in the Hereafter for showing off, so too there is a punishment for it in this world, the Prophet (sallAllaahu тАШalayhiwasallam): тАЬWhoever shows off, Allaah will expose him.тАЭ (Bukhaari).
